text: William Gaehler (February 15, 1896 - October 21, 1944) was an American canoeist who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics. He was born in New York City and died in Bronx, New York In 1936 he and his partner William Lofgren finished seventh in the K-2 10000 metres competition. ==References== *Sports- reference.com profile Category:1896 births Category:1944 deaths Category:Sportspeople from New York City Category:American male canoeists Category:Canoeists at the 1936 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic canoeists of the United States
